INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (598126845, 'officer_flavor_text_80003', '<color=#40CFFF>CLASS:</color> COMMAND
<color=#40CFFF>GROUP:</color> STRANGE NEW WORLDS
<color=#40CFFF>FACTION:</color> KLINGON

Captain D’Chok is one of Spock’s oldest friends. They first met during a diplomatic incident between Starfleet and the Klingon Defense Force, at the Dilithium mining planet of Cajitar IV. A rogue syndicate known as the Broken Circle tried to restart the Klingon War for personal gain, via a false flag attack on D’Chok’s vessel. Spock prevented the attack by destroying the false Federation starship. When D’Chok questioned his motivations, Spock suggested they open a barrel of bloodwine to conclude their discussion and show that he could be trusted. D’Chok was impressed at this suggestion from a Vulcan, and was eager to see the results in person. 

Since then, D’Chok has continued to excel in the Klingon military, being particularly noted for his genial personality and diplomatic qualities - especially towards non-Klingons. It is surely only a matter of time before Chancellor L’Rell promotes him to the rank of General.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (598126845, 'officer_name_80003', 'SNW D''Chok', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
